00:24:37.700 --> 00:24:40.050
No, but thanks.

517
00:24:40.400 --> 00:24:42.500
Okay, well, I'm right up here.

518
00:24:42.600 --> 00:24:43.800
I'm just studying for the bar exam.

519
00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:48.000
So, if you need anything, just holler at me.

520
00:24:48.100 --> 00:24:50.900
- Okay.
- Anything. All right?

521
00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:53.000
I'll get it for you.

522
00:24:56.400 --> 00:24:57.800
My name is Rudy Baylor.

523
00:24:57.900 --> 00:24:59.400
Kelly Riker. Nice to meet you.

524
00:24:59.500 --> 00:25:02.350
Kelly, it's nice to meet you, too.

525
00:25:02.450 --> 00:25:04.400
Why don't you sit down?

526
00:25:04.500 --> 00:25:07.300
Go ahead. Take a seat.

527
00:25:12.950 --> 00:25:16.000
What school do you go to?

528
00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:18.950
I went to Austin Peay

529
00:25:19.050 --> 00:25:21.600
and then law school at Memphis state.

530
00:25:24.400 --> 00:25:26.800
I always wanted to go to college,

531
00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:31.100
but it didn't work out.

532
00:25:31.200 --> 00:25:33.000
- Did you?
- Yeah.

533
00:25:33.100 --> 00:25:34.450
I always thought I'd go,

534
00:25:34.550 --> 00:25:36.250
but it didn't work out.

535
00:25:36.350 --> 00:25:39.300
What kind of lawyer do you want to be?

536
00:25:39.400 --> 00:25:44.000
Well, I enjoy trial work, so...

537
00:25:44.400 --> 00:25:47.500
I'd like to spend my days in the courtroom.

538
00:25:49.000 --> 00:25:51.450
Defending criminals?

539
00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:54.450
Maybe. Maybe.

540
00:25:54.550 --> 00:25:57.500
They're entitled to a good defense.

541
00:25:57.600 --> 00:25:59.850
They have a right to their day in court.

542
00:25:59.950 --> 00:26:01.800
Murderers?

543
00:26:04.350 --> 00:26:08.000
Most murderers can't afford a private lawyer.

544
00:26:10.550 --> 00:26:13.100
Rapists and...

545
00:26:13.200 --> 00:26:16.000
...child molesters?

546
00:26:17.700 --> 00:26:19.300
No.

547
00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:22.200
Men who beat their wives?

548
00:26:34.150 --> 00:26:37.300
Criminal work is a real rare specialty.

549
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:40.550
I'll probably be doing more...

550
00:26:40.650 --> 00:26:43.200
...civil litigation.

551
00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:45.550
Like lawsuits and stuff.

552
00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:47.000
- Right.
- Yeah.

553
00:26:50.700 --> 00:26:53.450
- Excuse me.
- Mm-hm.

554
00:27:01.100 --> 00:27:02.200
Rudy Baylor.

555
00:27:02.300 --> 00:27:04.250
Hey! Hey, there. It's me.

556
00:27:04.350 --> 00:27:05.500
What're you doing?

557
00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:07.500
How's the fishing going?

558
00:27:08.700 --> 00:27:10.000
It's going well.

559
00:27:10.100 --> 00:27:12.100
I'm actually talking to the prospect right now.

560
00:27:12.200 --> 00:27:14.500
<i>Well, you better sign her up.</i>

561
00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:17.500
<i>What... Rudy? Rudy, can you hear me?</i>

562
00:27:17.600 --> 00:27:19.900
- I enjoyed meeting you.
- <i>Rudy?</i>

563
00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:22.400
Yeah, thanks for the company.

564
00:27:22.700 --> 00:27:24.800
Hey, tomorrow night?

565
00:27:24.900 --> 00:27:27.050
Maybe.

566
00:27:42.100 --> 00:27:43.800
Time's up. Pencils down.

567
00:27:43.900 --> 00:27:45.800
Please pass your test booklets to your right,

568
00:27:45.900 --> 00:27:47.700
so that your proctors may gather them up.

569
00:27:47.800 --> 00:27:49.650
<i>In my first year at law school,</i>

570
00:27:49.750 --> 00:27:51.850
<i>everybody loved everybody else,</i>

571
00:27:51.950 --> 00:27:53.900
<i>because we were all studying the law.</i>

572
00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:56.450
<i>And the law was a noble thing.</i>

573
00:27:56.550 --> 00:27:58.300
<i>By my third year,</i>

574
00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:01.100
<i>you were lucky if you weren't
murdered in your sleep.</i>

575
00:28:01.200 --> 00:28:02.300
<i>People stole exams,</i>

576
00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:04.650
<i>hid research materials from the library,</i>

577
00:28:04.750 --> 00:28:06.700
<i>and lied to the professors.</i>

578
00:28:09.300 --> 00:28:12.250
<i>Such is the nature of the profession.</i>

579
00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:18.600
Right here.

580
00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:21.000
<i>Half an hour ago, her husband came in</i>

581
00:28:21.100 --> 00:28:22.950
<i>and threw a bowl of soup at her,</i>

582
00:28:23.050 --> 00:28:25.700
<i>because she just won't get it through
her head how much he loves her.</i>

583
00:28:25.800 --> 00:28:28.000
This is my room.

584
00:28:29.050 --> 00:28:32.000
<i>Pregnant at 18, married,
then a miscarriage,</i>

585
00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:34.000
<i>probably because he beat her up,</i>

586
00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:36.100
<i>and still, she can't leave him.</i>

587
00:28:36.200 --> 00:28:38.450
You are gonna have to help me.

588
00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:39.800
<i>Everything I've ever seen</i>

589
00:28:39.900 --> 00:28:42.200
<i>tells me that this girl is a loser,</i>

590
00:28:42.300 --> 00:28:45.100
<i>scarred and broken and
maybe even dangerous.</i>

591
00:28:45.200 --> 00:28:47.950
<i>But I've never really seen
anyone like her before.</i>

592
00:28:48.050 --> 00:28:49.200
<i>And instead of running away,</i>

593
00:28:49.300 --> 00:28:52.400
<i>all I want to do is protect her.</i>

594
00:29:14.550 --> 00:29:18.000
Visiting hours are over, hon.
You kids need to wrap it up.

595
00:29:38.850 --> 00:29:40.500
So...

596
00:29:40.900 --> 00:29:43.200
He should be shot.

597
00:29:43.300 --> 00:29:46.550
Any man who'd beat his wife
with an aluminum bat

598
00:29:46.650 --> 00:29:48.000
needs to be shot.

599
00:29:49.550 --> 00:29:51.450
How did you find out?

600
00:29:51.550 --> 00:29:53.800
There are police reports,
there are ambulance reports,

601
00:29:53.900 --> 00:29:56.300
there are hospital records.

602
00:29:56.400 --> 00:29:57.850
How long are you gonna wait, Kelly,

603
00:29:57.950 --> 00:30:01.300
until he decides to hit you
in the head with that bat of his?

604
00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:03.800
'Cause that could kill you, you know.
That'd be it.

605
00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:05.250
A couple of good shots to the skull,

606
00:30:05.350 --> 00:30:06.300
- and that would be it.
- Stop it!

607
00:30:06.400 --> 00:30:09.000
Don't tell me how it feels.

608
00:30:15.550 --> 00:30:17.300
Look at me, Kelly.

609
00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:19.300
Can I ask you something?

610
00:30:22.950 --> 00:30:26.200
Do you have a father or a brother?

611
00:30:27.900 --> 00:30:29.200
Why?

612
00:30:30.250 --> 00:30:33.300
Because if my daughter got beat
the way your husband beat you,

613
00:30:33.400 --> 00:30:36.000
I swear to God I'd break his neck.

614
00:30:38.100 --> 00:30:39.650
No big brother?

615
00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:43.650
No.

616
00:30:46.750 --> 00:30:50.000
No one to take care of me, you know?

617
00:30:54.400 --> 00:30:58.400
Kelly, I'll try to help you any way I can,

618
00:30:58.500 --> 00:31:01.950
but you have to file for divorce.

619
00:31:03.050 --> 00:31:06.550
Do it now while you're in the hospital
being treated for the last beating.

620
00:31:06.800 --> 00:31:08.100
It'll sail through.

621
00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:10.950
What better proof is there than that?

622
00:31:11.050 --> 00:31:15.300
I... can't file for a divorce.

623
00:31:16.250 --> 00:31:18.250
Why not?

624
00:31:18.350 --> 00:31:20.700
Because he'll kill me.

625
00:31:22.550 --> 00:31:25.550
He tells me so all the time.

626
00:31:28.300 --> 00:31:30.300
That's not gonna happen.

627
00:31:30.500 --> 00:31:34.500
Could you pass me a pillow,
please, and put it under my foot?

628
00:31:35.050 --> 00:31:37.000
There's one over there.

629
00:31:46.250 --> 00:31:47.500
Here.

630
00:31:50.250 --> 00:31:52.300
- That okay?
- Yeah.

631
00:31:52.400 --> 00:31:54.100
Yeah? All right.

632
00:31:54.200 --> 00:31:56.150
Could you pass me my gown, too, please?

633
00:31:56.250 --> 00:31:57.600
Yeah.

634
00:31:58.850 --> 00:32:00.550
Thanks.

635
00:32:00.650 --> 00:32:02.850
You need some help putting it on?

636
00:32:02.950 --> 00:32:05.100
No. Just turn around.

637
00:32:05.200 --> 00:32:07.000
All right.

638
00:32:26.450 --> 00:32:27.550
Hey!

639
00:32:27.650 --> 00:32:29.250
Oh! Who are you?

640
00:32:29.350 --> 00:32:30.950
I live here. Who the hell are you?

641
00:32:31.050 --> 00:32:33.600
Oh, my gosh! I'm Delbert's wife.

642
00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:35.000
Delbert? Who the hell is Delbert?

643
00:32:35.100 --> 00:32:36.200
What do you... How did you get in here?

644
00:32:36.300 --> 00:32:37.700
Birdie gave me the key.

645
00:32:37.800 --> 00:32:38.700
Yes. Who are you?

646
00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:41.050
I am the person who lives here.
Do you understand that?

647
00:32:41.150 --> 00:32:42.300
You have no right to be in here.

648
00:32:42.400 --> 00:32:43.500
- This is a private residence.
- Oh, yeah, right!

649
00:32:43.600 --> 00:32:47.500
Some place. Get a grip.
Birdie wants to see you.

650
00:32:50.700 --> 00:32:52.150
"Agreements are permanent,

651
00:32:52.250 --> 00:32:55.700
"and restrictions mentioned above herein..."

652
00:32:55.800 --> 00:32:57.350
What is this?

653
00:32:57.450 --> 00:32:59.350
Well, you must be the lawyer.

654
00:32:59.450 --> 00:33:00.400
I'm Rudy Baylor.

655
00:33:00.500 --> 00:33:03.000
I'm Delbert Birdsong, Birdie's youngest.

656
00:33:03.100 --> 00:33:04.300
He yelled at me.

657
00:33:04.400 --> 00:33:06.600
He told me to get out of his apartment.

658
00:33:06.700 --> 00:33:08.800
- That so?
- You're damn right that's so.

659
00:33:08.900 --> 00:33:10.300
That goes for the both of you.

660
00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:12.350
I don't want neither one of you
up there going through my stuff.

661
00:33:12.450 --> 00:33:13.350
That's private property.

662
00:33:13.450 --> 00:33:14.700
I come home to check on mama,

663
00:33:14.800 --> 00:33:17.650
and, damn, she's got a stinkin' lawyer
livin' with her.

664
00:33:17.750 --> 00:33:20.600
You been messin' with my mama's will?

665
00:33:20.700 --> 00:33:22.900
Well, she's your mama.
Why don't you ask her?

666
00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:26.600
She won't say a word.

667
00:33:26.700 --> 00:33:27.800
Oh, well...

668
00:33:27.900 --> 00:33:30.450
then neither can I.

669
00:33:30.550 --> 00:33:33.200
That's a lawyer-client privilege.

670
00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:40.250
But I tell you what.

671
00:33:42.950 --> 00:33:46.250
- I made a couple of phone calls.
- Mm-hm.

672
00:33:46.350 --> 00:33:48.000
- Verifying some accounts.
- Mm-hm.

673
00:33:48.100 --> 00:33:50.550
Your mama's second husband

674
00:33:50.650 --> 00:33:53.000
left her an enormous fortune.

675
00:33:53.100 --> 00:33:54.400
How big?

676
00:33:54.500 --> 00:33:56.650
Big.

677
00:33:56.750 --> 00:33:58.050
Big.

678
00:33:58.150 --> 00:34:00.350
I hope you're not meddling, boy.

679
00:34:01.650 --> 00:34:05.250
Mama, wouldn't you just love
to come and visit with us

680
00:34:05.350 --> 00:34:07.100
down in Florida for a while?

681
00:34:07.200 --> 00:34:09.050
You'd love it down there, mama.

682
00:34:09.150 --> 00:34:11.100
Mama, come on back in
and get some cake, mama.

683
00:34:11.200 --> 00:34:12.400
I'll get her some milk.

684
00:34:12.500 --> 00:34:14.200
We're close to the fountain of youth.

685
00:34:14.300 --> 00:34:18.850
We ain't but 33 miles away
and 180 miles from Disney world.

686
00:34:43.050 --> 00:34:44.950
How're you feeling, Donny Ray?

687
00:34:45.050 --> 00:34:46.100
Great.

688
00:34:46.200 --> 00:34:48.700
Don't I look fantastic?

689
00:34:48.800 --> 00:34:49.950
You feel up to this?

690
00:34:50.050 --> 00:34:51.700
Yeah. Let's go already.

691
00:34:51.800 --> 00:34:53.100
All right.

692
00:34:55.250 --> 00:34:59.000
<i>A lawyer's not supposed to become
personally involved with his client.</i>

693
00:34:59.400 --> 00:35:01.900
<i>But there's all kinds of lawyers.</i>

694
00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:04.250
<i>And all kinds of clients, too.</i>

695
00:35:18.750 --> 00:35:20.400
You okay, baby?

696
00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:36.700
<b>Riker!</b>

697
00:35:36.800 --> 00:35:39.350
Can I get you guys anything else?

698
00:35:40.450 --> 00:35:42.300
You want something?

699
00:35:42.700 --> 00:35:45.650
I'll have a shot of Jack Daniels, please.

700
00:35:47.650 --> 00:35:50.000
What's it gonna do, kill me?

701
00:35:52.850 --> 00:35:55.450
- Miss Birdie, this is my friend Donny Ray.
- Hello.

702
00:35:55.550 --> 00:35:59.550
Oh, Donny Ray, I'm so glad
to have you come over and visit.

703
00:35:59.650 --> 00:36:01.150
Hello, Miss Birdie.

704
00:36:01.250 --> 00:36:02.900
Where... Oh!

705
00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:04.150
There you go.

706
00:36:04.250 --> 00:36:06.300
You just come right over here and sit down.

707
00:36:06.400 --> 00:36:08.050
Just have a rest.

708
00:36:09.650 --> 00:36:11.100
You have me all...

709
00:36:11.200 --> 00:36:12.800
...blocked off here.

710
00:36:12.900 --> 00:36:14.100
Well...

711
00:36:26.450 --> 00:36:29.200
Sorry, Miss Birdie. I got to take
a break. My back's killing me.

712
00:36:29.300 --> 00:36:31.950
I almost forgot. This came for you.

713
00:36:37.150 --> 00:36:38.400
Oh, my God!

714
00:36:38.500 --> 00:36:40.450
Oh! Isn't it exciting?

715
00:36:41.550 --> 00:36:43.900
I'm so proud of you.

716
00:36:44.000 --> 00:36:45.800
- I passed the bar.
- All right.

717
00:36:46.150 --> 00:36:48.550
Hey, come on. Here's to Rudy.

718
00:36:48.650 --> 00:36:51.550
Congratulations on passing the bar.

719
00:36:51.650 --> 00:36:53.350
What the hell is that?

720
00:36:53.450 --> 00:36:54.900
Iced tea.

721
00:36:56.250 --> 00:36:58.600
- Congratulations, Rudy.
- Thanks, Deck.

722
00:36:58.700 --> 00:37:00.000
That's some good work, boys.

723
00:37:00.100 --> 00:37:02.100
I got a check today from
the Van Landel settlement.

724
00:37:02.200 --> 00:37:03.900
I'm giving you boys a bonus.

725
00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:06.400
5,500 each.

726
00:37:06.500 --> 00:37:07.500
Thank you.

727
00:37:07.600 --> 00:37:10.000
Sign up some more cases, huh?

728
00:37:10.850 --> 00:37:11.900
Okay.

729
00:37:13.450 --> 00:37:17.250
So, are we gonna be ready
for tomorrow morning?

730
00:37:17.350 --> 00:37:18.850
9 o'clock?

731
00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:25.650
We're gonna argue Great
Benefit's motion to dismiss.

732
00:37:25.750 --> 00:37:28.900
Yeah, I think we're ready. We're ready.

733
00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:32.800
So, Deck and I have been
going over it. I think we're ready.

734
00:37:32.900 --> 00:37:35.850
I hope so, because I might...

735
00:37:35.950 --> 00:37:39.450
I might have you handle
some of that argument, Rudy.

736
00:37:41.100 --> 00:37:45.400
It would be awfully embarrassing
if we lose this case

737
00:37:45.500 --> 00:37:47.000
on a dismissal.

738
00:37:47.100 --> 00:37:49.250
Boss?

739
00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:51.150
Okay, I got to go.

740
00:37:52.550 --> 00:37:54.000
Food's on me.

741
00:37:54.100 --> 00:37:56.650
Enjoy your meat.

742
00:37:56.750 --> 00:37:58.900
Thanks a lot, Bruiser. Appreciate it.

743
00:38:05.450 --> 00:38:07.050
Something's about to go down.

744
00:38:07.150 --> 00:38:08.650
I'm sure of it.

745
00:38:09.650 --> 00:38:13.000
He never split money like that before.

746
00:38:13.100 --> 00:38:16.300
What do you think's behind his generosity?

747
00:38:16.400 --> 00:38:18.450
Come on, man.

748
00:38:19.500 --> 00:38:20.700
Oh, yeah?

749
00:38:22.550 --> 00:38:23.750
Here.

750
00:38:25.250 --> 00:38:29.000
Yesterday, one of Bruiser's ex-partners
testified before a grand jury.

751
00:38:29.100 --> 00:38:30.850
I think he's cut a deal.

752
00:38:30.950 --> 00:38:33.000
It's just a matter of time
before he's singing on Bruiser.

753
00:38:33.100 --> 00:38:34.950
- So what? So what?
- So...

754
00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:37.900
You're gonna have to make a move.

755
00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:40.900
Make a move? Deck, I just got here.

756
00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:44.200
Yeah? Well, things might get a little hot.

757
00:38:45.800 --> 00:38:47.700
Jury-tampering, tax evasion,

758
00:38:47.800 --> 00:38:49.550
money-skimming, you name it.

759
00:38:49.650 --> 00:38:51.250
I'm nervous, real nervous.

760
00:38:51.350 --> 00:38:54.250
Well, hey, what are you nervous about?
They can't arrest us.

761
00:38:54.350 --> 00:38:56.550
Listen...

762
00:38:56.650 --> 00:38:59.550
Supposing they come in with
subpoenas and hacksaws.

763
00:38:59.650 --> 00:39:00.850
Huh? They can do that.

764
00:39:00.950 --> 00:39:03.850
They've been known to do
that in racketeering cases.

765
00:39:03.950 --> 00:39:05.650
They come in, they confiscate the files,

766
00:39:05.750 --> 00:39:06.700
they haul the computers out.

767
00:39:06.900 --> 00:39:08.200
What's that leave us?

768
00:39:08.300 --> 00:39:09.850
I'm not worried about being arrested.

769
00:39:09.950 --> 00:39:11.500
I'm worried about my job.

770
00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:14.200
All right, so what are you saying here?

771
00:39:14.300 --> 00:39:16.500
Let's bolt.

772
00:39:17.500 --> 00:39:19.350
How much money you got?

773
00:39:19.450 --> 00:39:22.300
I got... $5,500.

774
00:39:22.400 --> 00:39:23.700
Me, too.

775
00:39:23.800 --> 00:39:25.800
We can rent a small office,

776
00:39:25.900 --> 00:39:27.800
$500 a month.

777
