01:21:47.700 --> 01:21:51.300
Hell, I wanted to sue for a whole lot more.

1558
01:21:52.450 --> 01:21:55.050
What would you do with the money?

1559
01:21:55.150 --> 01:21:57.000
If this jury awards you $10 million,

1560
01:21:57.100 --> 01:21:58.500
what're you gonna do with the money?

1561
01:21:58.600 --> 01:22:02.000
I'm gonna give it to the
American leukemia society.

1563
01:22:02.550 --> 01:22:04.250
Every cent.

1564
01:22:05.450 --> 01:22:08.900
I don't want a dime of your stinking money.

1565
01:22:09.000 --> 01:22:13.000
Realize you are under oath, Mrs. Black.

1566
01:22:13.100 --> 01:22:15.250
Approach the witness, your honor?

1567
01:22:15.350 --> 01:22:16.500
You may.

1568
01:22:16.600 --> 01:22:19.650
Mrs. Black, I want you
to read from the policy.

1570
01:22:19.750 --> 01:22:24.000
Page 16, section "K",
paragraph 14, item "E",

1571
01:22:24.100 --> 01:22:27.000
in which the insurance company
has in plain English wording said

1573
01:22:27.100 --> 01:22:30.350
that it will not pay for
experimental procedures.

1574
01:22:30.450 --> 01:22:33.150
Now, your lawsuit says

1575
01:22:33.250 --> 01:22:35.500
that your son would have
been saved if he had had

1576
01:22:35.600 --> 01:22:36.900
a bone marrow transplant.

1577
01:22:37.000 --> 01:22:38.950
Isn't it a fact, Mrs. Black,

1578
01:22:39.050 --> 01:22:40.450
that there are only 7,000

1579
01:22:40.550 --> 01:22:43.500
bone marrow transplants performed
a year in the United States?

1581
01:22:43.600 --> 01:22:45.650
Less than 200 in the state of Tennessee.

1582
01:22:45.750 --> 01:22:46.900
Objection, your honor.

1583
01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:48.150
He's leading the witness.

1584
01:22:48.250 --> 01:22:50.650
This is cross-examination.
Leading is allowed.

1585
01:22:50.750 --> 01:22:52.550
Overruled,

1586
01:22:52.650 --> 01:22:54.500
as to leading.

1587
01:22:54.600 --> 01:22:59.000
So, it was not covered by the policy.

1588
01:22:59.100 --> 01:23:00.050
Now, Mrs. Black,

1589
01:23:00.150 --> 01:23:02.850
who was it...

1590
01:23:02.950 --> 01:23:06.200
Who was it first diagnosed
your son's condition?

1591
01:23:07.500 --> 01:23:09.450
Well, at the very beginning,

1592
01:23:09.550 --> 01:23:12.950
our doctor, Dr. page.

1593
01:23:13.050 --> 01:23:15.400
That would be your family physician?

1594
01:23:15.500 --> 01:23:17.100
Yes, sir, it would.

1595
01:23:17.200 --> 01:23:18.550
Is he a good doctor?

1596
01:23:18.650 --> 01:23:20.350
He's a very good doctor.

1597
01:23:20.450 --> 01:23:22.900
And is it not true, Mrs. Black,

1598
01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:25.400
that this capable, truthful man

1599
01:23:25.500 --> 01:23:28.350
told you repeatedly
that a bone marrow transplant

1600
01:23:28.450 --> 01:23:29.450
would do your son no good,

1601
01:23:29.550 --> 01:23:32.500
because of the type of leukemia he had?

1602
01:23:33.950 --> 01:23:35.650
Well, no.

1603
01:23:35.750 --> 01:23:37.050
No, he did not.

1604
01:23:37.150 --> 01:23:38.100
He didn't say that.

1605
01:23:38.200 --> 01:23:40.800
Not like that, to me.

1606
01:23:42.250 --> 01:23:43.400
Approach the witness, your honor?

1607
01:23:43.500 --> 01:23:44.900
You may.

1608
01:23:45.350 --> 01:23:50.500
Mrs. Black, is this not
Dr. page's letterhead?

1609
01:23:50.600 --> 01:23:53.700
And at the bottom there,
is that not his signature?

1610
01:23:53.800 --> 01:23:55.550
- He can't do that.
- <i>Yes, it is.</i>

1611
01:23:55.650 --> 01:23:57.000
- Why?
- <i>And is this not addressed to you?</i>

1612
01:23:57.100 --> 01:23:58.500
Because he can't introduce
evidence that way.

1613
01:23:58.600 --> 01:24:00.400
- Plus it's hearsay.
- <i>Yes, sir.</i>

1614
01:24:00.500 --> 01:24:02.300
Objection, your honor.

1615
01:24:02.400 --> 01:24:06.250
A letter from the Blacks' family physician

1616
01:24:06.350 --> 01:24:08.400
to Mr. Drummond is inadmissible.

1617
01:24:08.500 --> 01:24:10.350
That is quite correct, your honor.

1618
01:24:10.450 --> 01:24:13.700
And I'm not asking for this letter
to be admitted into evidence.

1620
01:24:13.800 --> 01:24:16.450
I'm simply asking that this witness

1621
01:24:16.550 --> 01:24:17.550
be allowed to read the letter

1622
01:24:17.650 --> 01:24:19.350
under rule 612 of the
Tennessee rules of evidence.

1623
01:24:19.450 --> 01:24:20.700
612.

1624
01:24:20.800 --> 01:24:22.550
So her recollection can be refreshed.
That's all.

1625
01:24:22.650 --> 01:24:25.050
Mr. Baylor, what do you say?

1626
01:24:25.150 --> 01:24:26.700
I don't know, your honor.

1627
01:24:26.800 --> 01:24:27.900
I just object to this.

1628
01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:31.750
And also we were not furnished this letter

1629
01:24:31.850 --> 01:24:33.200
in pre-trial discovery.

1630
01:24:33.300 --> 01:24:35.300
What do you say to that, Mr. Drummond?

1631
01:24:35.400 --> 01:24:37.550
Your honor, I had no idea
this letter would be needed.

1632
01:24:37.650 --> 01:24:41.050
I expected this lady to tell the truth
about what her doctor told her.

1634
01:24:43.050 --> 01:24:45.200
Anything else, Mr. Baylor?

1635
01:24:47.300 --> 01:24:48.800
No.

1636
01:24:50.900 --> 01:24:54.750
Mr. Drummond, I'm gonna
give you a little latitude,

1638
01:24:54.850 --> 01:24:56.500
but don't stray too far.

1639
01:24:56.600 --> 01:24:59.100
Very well, your honor. Now, Mrs. Black,

1640
01:24:59.200 --> 01:25:01.700
does that letter refresh your recollection

1641
01:25:01.800 --> 01:25:04.000
as to whether or not
Donny Ray's leukemia

1642
01:25:04.100 --> 01:25:06.650
was the kind that could be helped
by a bone marrow transplant?

1644
01:25:06.750 --> 01:25:09.000
Well, see, now, he is not a specialist.

1645
01:25:09.100 --> 01:25:10.000
But he is a licensed,

1646
01:25:10.100 --> 01:25:13.450
experienced, capable physician

1647
01:25:13.550 --> 01:25:16.150
who lovingly told you time and time again

1648
01:25:16.250 --> 01:25:19.400
what you quite understandably
did not want to accept...

1649
01:25:19.500 --> 01:25:22.300
that your son was going to die of leukemia

1650
01:25:22.400 --> 01:25:25.000
despite the best efforts of medical science.

1651
01:25:25.100 --> 01:25:26.650
Is that not true?

1652
01:25:26.750 --> 01:25:29.100
But he wasn't a specialist.

1653
01:25:29.200 --> 01:25:30.500
I didn't believe him.

1654
01:25:30.600 --> 01:25:33.700
Not only did you not believe him, ma'am,

1655
01:25:33.800 --> 01:25:35.550
but you were less than truthful with me

1656
01:25:35.650 --> 01:25:37.700
and with this jury moments ago

1657
01:25:37.800 --> 01:25:39.200
when you told us under oath

1658
01:25:39.300 --> 01:25:42.000
that Dr. page never said that your son

1659
01:25:42.100 --> 01:25:44.550
had the type of leukemia
that could not be treated

1660
01:25:44.650 --> 01:25:46.000
by a bone marrow transplant.

1661
01:25:46.100 --> 01:25:48.150
I believe your exact words were...

1662
01:25:48.250 --> 01:25:50.350
"He never said that.

1663
01:25:50.450 --> 01:25:51.550
"Not like that

1664
01:25:51.650 --> 01:25:53.400
"to me."

1665
01:25:53.500 --> 01:25:56.400
He wasn't a specialist.

1666
01:25:56.500 --> 01:25:58.750
I just wanted Donny Ray

1667
01:25:58.850 --> 01:26:03.000
to have the best medical
treatment available.

1668
01:26:03.500 --> 01:26:05.500
You'd do the same thing.

1669
01:26:06.700 --> 01:26:08.750
Of course, ma'am.

1670
01:26:09.000 --> 01:26:11.500
Of course.

1671
01:26:11.600 --> 01:26:13.250
That'll be all.

1672
01:26:13.500 --> 01:26:15.000
You honor.

1672
01:26:15.200 --> 01:26:17.800
You may step down, Mrs. Black.

1673
01:26:25.350 --> 01:26:27.750
I didn't do very good, did I?

1674
01:26:27.850 --> 01:26:30.400
Oh, no, no, you did fine. You did fine.

1676
01:26:30.500 --> 01:26:34.350
It's all right. The jury can see
exactly what he's up to.

1678
01:26:34.450 --> 01:26:35.850
- The jury can see what he's up to.
- Don't worry about it.

1679
01:26:35.950 --> 01:26:37.500
- I need a smoke.
- I know you do.

1681
01:26:37.600 --> 01:26:38.750
We're gonna get to that later.

1684
01:26:42.450 --> 01:26:45.350
I hope he hasn't changed the locks.

1685
01:26:45.450 --> 01:26:47.000
Are you scared?

1686
01:26:47.100 --> 01:26:49.150
Yeah.

1687
01:26:51.250 --> 01:26:53.000
Let's do it.

1689
01:27:19.750 --> 01:27:21.550
What a pig!

1690
01:27:22.450 --> 01:27:23.600
I'm sorry.

1691
01:27:23.700 --> 01:27:26.000
Hurry, Kelly. Come on.

1692
01:27:29.100 --> 01:27:31.550
There's more of my stuff in the closet.

1693
01:27:40.000 --> 01:27:42.500
Hey, you can't take everything, Kelly.

1695
01:27:57.900 --> 01:28:00.050
Oh, no!

1696
01:28:00.500 --> 01:28:03.350
Hey! Hello!

1697
01:28:03.450 --> 01:28:05.050
I'm home!

1698
01:28:05.900 --> 01:28:07.750
Well, what do you know?

1699
01:28:07.850 --> 01:28:10.400
What do we have here?

1700
01:28:10.500 --> 01:28:12.300
What you two been doing in here, huh?

1701
01:28:12.400 --> 01:28:14.200
Hey, take it easy, all right?

1702
01:28:14.300 --> 01:28:16.000
Come on, tell me. I'm your husband.
Remember that, huh?

1704
01:28:16.100 --> 01:28:18.000
- Take it easy, Buddy.
- You shut up!

1706
01:28:18.100 --> 01:28:19.750
Hey, listen, Buddy, all right? Listen.

1707
01:28:19.850 --> 01:28:20.750
I ain't listening to nothing!

1708
01:28:20.850 --> 01:28:22.700
Take it easy. Take it...

1710
01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:24.600
You hurt me, baby.

1711
01:28:24.700 --> 01:28:25.850
You hurt me so bad!

1713
01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:29.350
Why are you doing this to me?!

1714
01:28:29.450 --> 01:28:30.600
No, Cliff!

1715
01:28:35.150 --> 01:28:36.700
Run!

1716
01:29:09.450 --> 01:29:11.050
Rudy! Rudy!

1717
01:29:11.150 --> 01:29:13.250
Cliff, you idiot, what are you doing?!

1719
01:29:13.350 --> 01:29:14.450
You see what you did?

1720
01:29:14.550 --> 01:29:15.900
- Kelly!
- You see what you did?

1721
01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:17.200
Is this what you wanted?

1722
01:29:18.000 --> 01:29:21.000
It's not my fault! I love you! I love you!

1724
01:29:33.950 --> 01:29:35.600
Rudy!

1726
01:29:41.200 --> 01:29:42.700
Stop it, Rudy!

1727
01:29:42.800 --> 01:29:44.300
Stop.

1729
01:29:45.700 --> 01:29:48.500
Give me the bat and leave.

1730
01:29:48.600 --> 01:29:50.300
What?

1731
01:29:51.850 --> 01:29:54.150
Give me the bat and leave.

1732
01:29:54.250 --> 01:29:56.800
You were not here tonight.

1733
01:29:56.900 --> 01:29:58.850
Give me the bat.

1734
01:30:13.200 --> 01:30:14.200
Go, Rudy.

1735
01:30:14.300 --> 01:30:16.400
You were not here tonight.

1738
01:30:53.300 --> 01:30:55.150
He's finally killed her.

1739
01:30:55.250 --> 01:30:57.350
No, it's him. He's dead.

1740
01:30:57.450 --> 01:30:59.300
- You sure?
- Just saw her.

1742
01:30:59.400 --> 01:31:01.600
- How'd it happen?
- I don't know, but...

1744
01:31:01.700 --> 01:31:03.350
<i>They say when you commit a murder,</i>

1745
01:31:03.450 --> 01:31:04.750
<i>you make at least 25 mistakes,</i>

1746
01:31:04.850 --> 01:31:07.950
<i>and later you're lucky
if you remember 5 of 'em.</i>

1747
01:31:08.050 --> 01:31:09.050
<i>It was self-defense,</i>

1748
01:31:09.150 --> 01:31:11.150
<i>but I can't get past the fact that he's dead.</i>

1749
01:31:11.250 --> 01:31:14.000
<i>And the mistakes are piling up
in my mind so fast, I can't think.</i>

1750
01:31:14.100 --> 01:31:15.500
This way, ma'am.

1751
01:31:17.250 --> 01:31:18.400
<i>But Kelly knew.</i>

1752
01:31:18.500 --> 01:31:20.050
<i>She knew what to do.</i>

1753
01:31:20.150 --> 01:31:21.650
<i>She knew it was time.</i>

1754
01:31:23.600 --> 01:31:26.350
<i>With everything that was happening
and all that was at stake,</i>

1756
01:31:26.450 --> 01:31:30.000
<i>her first thought was for my safety.</i>

1757
01:31:30.500 --> 01:31:33.150
<i>And I left her in there all alone.</i>

1758
01:31:34.600 --> 01:31:36.350
Damn it!

1759
01:31:36.450 --> 01:31:37.600
God damn you, Kelly!

1760
01:31:37.700 --> 01:31:39.350
What the hell's going on here?

1761
01:31:39.450 --> 01:31:41.450
What the hell did you do?

1762
01:31:48.850 --> 01:31:50.450
You killed my son!

1763
01:31:50.550 --> 01:31:51.750
God damn you!

1765
01:32:26.650 --> 01:32:29.100
Excuse me, I'm her lawyer.

1766
01:32:29.200 --> 01:32:32.100
I insist on being here
while she's being questioned.

1767
01:32:32.200 --> 01:32:33.600
This is your attorney?

1768
01:32:33.700 --> 01:32:35.300
Yes, sir.

1769
01:32:37.150 --> 01:32:40.050
I want her released to my custody.

1770
01:32:40.150 --> 01:32:41.300
I can't do that.

1771
01:32:41.400 --> 01:32:43.250
I don't know what kind of lawyer you are,

1772
01:32:43.350 --> 01:32:44.850
but we got a dead body here,

1773
01:32:44.950 --> 01:32:47.750
and bond needs to be set by a judge.

1774
01:32:47.850 --> 01:32:49.350
I'm going to jail?

1775
01:32:49.450 --> 01:32:51.950
Well, can we arrange for a private cell?

1776
01:32:52.050 --> 01:32:54.300
Look, asshole, I don't run the jail.

1777
01:32:54.400 --> 01:32:56.300
You got a better way of doing things,

1778
01:32:56.400 --> 01:32:58.500
then you need to talk to the jailer.

1779
01:32:58.600 --> 01:33:00.800
They love lawyers down there, right?

1780
01:33:01.500 --> 01:33:03.350
Look...

1781
01:33:03.450 --> 01:33:05.300
If your lawyer here is worth his salt,

1782
01:33:05.400 --> 01:33:09.150
you'll be out of here sometime tomorrow,
if you can post bond, okay?

1784
01:33:11.350 --> 01:33:12.950
Okay.

1785
01:33:17.200 --> 01:33:19.500
- You got 5.
- Thank you.

1787
01:33:26.200 --> 01:33:27.950
They're watching us
through that window there,

1788
01:33:28.050 --> 01:33:30.700
and this room is probably bugged,

1789
01:33:30.800 --> 01:33:33.800
so just be careful what you say.

1790
01:33:33.900 --> 01:33:35.700
What does "manslaughter" mean?

1791
01:33:35.800 --> 01:33:38.650
It's just murder without the element of intent.

1792
01:33:38.750 --> 01:33:40.600
How much time could I get?

1793
01:33:40.700 --> 01:33:42.200
No, no, no, you have to be convicted first.

1794
01:33:42.300 --> 01:33:44.800
I'm not gonna let that happen.

1795
01:33:44.900 --> 01:33:47.750
That's not gonna happen.

1796
01:33:51.550 --> 01:33:55.200
Cross your wrists
behind you please, ma'am.

1797
01:33:59.500 --> 01:34:01.000
This way, ma'am.

1799
01:34:08.550 --> 01:34:10.100
Mr. Lufkin...

1800
01:34:10.200 --> 01:34:13.400
you are the Vice President of Claims
at Great Benefit, are you not?

1802
01:34:13.500 --> 01:34:14.500
Yes, I am.

1803
01:34:14.600 --> 01:34:15.400
Approach the witness, your honor?

1804
01:34:15.500 --> 01:34:17.000
You may.

1805
01:34:19.000 --> 01:34:21.200
You recognize this?

1806
01:34:21.500 --> 01:34:22.650
Go on.

1807
01:34:24.750 --> 01:34:26.900
Read that to the jury.

1808
01:34:29.600 --> 01:34:30.650
"Dear Mrs. Black,

1809
01:34:30.750 --> 01:34:34.000
"on 7 prior occasions this company
has denied your claim in writing.

1811
01:34:34.100 --> 01:34:35.700
"We now deny it
for the eighth and final time.

1812
01:34:35.800 --> 01:34:37.850
"You must be stupid, stupid, stupid.

1813
01:34:37.950 --> 01:34:39.600
"Sincerely Everett Lufkin,

1814
01:34:39.700 --> 01:34:41.400
"Vice President, Claims."

1815
01:34:41.500 --> 01:34:43.200
That's you?

1816
01:34:43.650 --> 01:34:44.900
Yes.

1817
01:34:47.250 --> 01:34:49.250
How do you explain that?

1818
01:34:54.350 --> 01:34:56.950
It was a difficult time for me personally.

1819
01:34:57.050 --> 01:34:59.550
I was under a lot of stress.

1820
01:34:59.650 --> 01:35:03.100
We had denied this claim 7 times before.

1821
01:35:03.200 --> 01:35:05.800
I was trying to be emphatic.

1822
01:35:05.900 --> 01:35:07.450
I snapped.

1823
01:35:07.550 --> 01:35:09.050
I regret having written the letter,

1824
01:35:09.150 --> 01:35:11.550
and I apologize.

1825
01:35:11.650 --> 01:35:14.350
Don't you think it's a little late
for an apology?

1827
01:35:16.000 --> 01:35:17.700
Maybe.

1828
01:35:17.800 --> 01:35:18.700
Maybe?

1829
01:35:18.800 --> 01:35:20.850
The boy is dead, isn't he?

1830
01:35:24.250 --> 01:35:26.800
Yes.

1831
01:35:26.900 --> 01:35:28.800
Now, Mr. Lufkin,

1832
01:35:28.900 --> 01:35:31.150
who is Jackie Lemancyzk?

1833
01:35:31.250 --> 01:35:37.100
Jackie Lemancyzk
is a former claims handler.

1834
01:35:37.200 --> 01:35:39.050
And did she work in your department?

1835
01:35:39.250 --> 01:35:40.050
Yes.

1836
01:35:40.150 --> 01:35:43.250
And when did she stop
working for Great Benefit?

1838
01:35:43.350 --> 01:35:46.050
I don't remember the day.

1839
01:35:46.150 --> 01:35:48.050
How about October 30th?

1840
01:35:48.150 --> 01:35:49.600
Sounds close.

1841
01:35:49.700 --> 01:35:51.900
And wasn't that just two days
before she was scheduled

1842
01:35:52.000 --> 01:35:53.850
to give a deposition in this case?

1843
01:35:53.950 --> 01:35:55.500
I really don't remember.

1844
01:35:55.600 --> 01:36:00.000
I'd like to refresh the witness'
recollection under rule 612.

1846
01:36:03.700 --> 01:36:05.050
October 30th.

1847
01:36:05.150 --> 01:36:06.250
Apparently.

1848
01:36:06.350 --> 01:36:07.450
And that was just two days
before she was scheduled

1849
01:36:07.550 --> 01:36:09.100
to give a deposition in this matter?

1850
01:36:09.200 --> 01:36:10.200
I guess so.

1851
01:36:10.300 --> 01:36:11.700
