02:03:33.500 --> 02:03:34.900
Yes, we have, your honor.

2422
02:03:35.000 --> 02:03:36.500
Is it written on paper,

2423
02:03:36.600 --> 02:03:37.950
according to my instructions?

2424
02:03:38.050 --> 02:03:39.600
Yes, sir.

2425
02:03:39.700 --> 02:03:41.400
Please read the verdict.

2426
02:03:42.950 --> 02:03:47.200
"We, the jury, find for the plaintiff

2427
02:03:47.300 --> 02:03:49.750
"and award actual damages

2428
02:03:49.850 --> 02:03:53.950
"in the amount of $150,000."

2430
02:03:57.300 --> 02:04:02.600
"And we, the jury, find for the plaintiff

2431
02:04:02.700 --> 02:04:05.150
"and award punitive damages

2432
02:04:05.250 --> 02:04:09.500
"in the amount of $50 million."

2435
02:04:24.950 --> 02:04:26.800
All rise.

2436
02:04:28.050 --> 02:04:29.500
<i>These people were trying to hide things</i>

2437
02:04:29.600 --> 02:04:32.250
<i>and were trying to get away
with something they were...</i>

2438
02:04:32.350 --> 02:04:33.500
<i>And they got caught at it.</i>

2439
02:04:33.600 --> 02:04:35.250
<i>Another remarkable part of the story,</i>

2440
02:04:35.350 --> 02:04:37.500
<i>the lead attorney on the case, Rudy Baylor,</i>

2441
02:04:37.600 --> 02:04:39.200
<i>was trying his first case.</i>

2442
02:04:39.300 --> 02:04:40.600
<i>That's a staggering verdict,</i>

2443
02:04:40.700 --> 02:04:42.600
<i>I think, by anybody's estimation.</i>

2444
02:04:42.700 --> 02:04:44.050
<i>It's certainly one of the largest...</i>

2445
02:04:44.150 --> 02:04:46.500
Well, not bad for a yard boy.

2446
02:04:46.600 --> 02:04:48.350
Well, it wasn't that difficult, really.

2447
02:04:48.450 --> 02:04:51.000
We just had a... great jury is what we had,

2448
02:04:51.100 --> 02:04:52.650
and the facts just fell into place.

2449
02:04:52.750 --> 02:04:55.600
- <i>$50 million in punitive damages.</i>
- $50 million?

2451
02:04:55.700 --> 02:04:56.650
Yeah.

2452
02:04:56.750 --> 02:04:58.250
How much do you get?

2453
02:04:58.350 --> 02:05:00.350
You get right to the point, don't you?

2454
02:05:00.450 --> 02:05:01.950
I'm sorry. It's not what I meant.

2455
02:05:02.050 --> 02:05:03.250
I know you didn't.

2456
02:05:03.350 --> 02:05:07.150
We get one third,
but the money's not in the bank yet.

2457
02:05:08.050 --> 02:05:09.500
I'll see you later.

2458
02:05:09.600 --> 02:05:11.500
You gonna leave this girl all alone?

2459
02:05:11.600 --> 02:05:13.150
Not for long.

2460
02:05:14.600 --> 02:05:17.300
Rudy. Rudy.

2461
02:05:17.400 --> 02:05:20.700
I've decided I'm gonna put
your name in my will.

2463
02:05:22.000 --> 02:05:25.300
You know what? You are just
too kind to me, Miss Birdie.

2464
02:05:29.200 --> 02:05:30.900
Hot off the newswire.

2465
02:05:31.000 --> 02:05:35.550
"Mr. Wilfred Keeley,
CEO of Great Benefit,

2466
02:05:35.650 --> 02:05:38.100
"was detained yesterday afternoon at JFK

2467
02:05:38.200 --> 02:05:41.150
"just after boarding a flight
bound for Heathrow.

2468
02:05:41.250 --> 02:05:42.650
"Traveling with his wife,

2469
02:05:42.750 --> 02:05:45.550
"they claimed to be sneaking
away for a quick holiday.

2470
02:05:45.650 --> 02:05:48.900
"However, they could not produce
the name of a hotel anywhere in Europe..."

2472
02:05:49.000 --> 02:05:50.250
<i>...at which they were expected.</i>

2473
02:05:50.350 --> 02:05:53.000
<i>At 5 p.m. today, insurance
company Great Benefit</i>

2474
02:05:53.100 --> 02:05:55.000
<i>filed for protection
under the bankruptcy code</i>

2475
02:05:55.100 --> 02:05:56.550
<i>in federal court in Cleveland.</i>

2476
02:05:56.650 --> 02:05:59.400
<i>Many states are now
investigating Great Benefit,</i>

2477
02:05:59.500 --> 02:06:01.850
<i>and a number of class-action
lawsuits have been filed.</i>

2478
02:06:02.000 --> 02:06:04.350
<i>For CNN, Jim Redmond reporting.</i>

2479
02:06:04.450 --> 02:06:05.850
Hello?

2480
02:06:05.950 --> 02:06:08.900
<i>Rudy, Leo Drummond here.</i>

2481
02:06:09.000 --> 02:06:13.000
It appears the company's been looted.

2482
02:06:13.600 --> 02:06:15.550
I'm sorry, Rudy.

2483
02:06:15.650 --> 02:06:18.850
I wanted you to get
every penny of that money.

2484
02:06:18.950 --> 02:06:21.850
<i>Everybody loses on this one.</i>

2485
02:06:21.950 --> 02:06:24.100
Wanted you to know.

2486
02:06:25.250 --> 02:06:27.100
Thank you, Mr. Drummond.

2487
02:06:28.300 --> 02:06:30.500
Great Benefit's like a bad slot machine,

2488
02:06:30.600 --> 02:06:32.600
never pays off.

2489
02:06:33.200 --> 02:06:35.150
We should have taken 175,000.

2490
02:06:35.250 --> 02:06:38.350
What the hell were we thinking?

2491
02:06:42.400 --> 02:06:44.350
It just got all twisted, didn't it?

2492
02:06:44.450 --> 02:06:47.300
This legal profession.

2493
02:06:47.400 --> 02:06:50.800
<i>Every lawyer in America
is talking about me right now.</i>

2495
02:06:50.900 --> 02:06:52.150
<i>But that doesn't exactly make me feel</i>

2496
02:06:52.250 --> 02:06:55.000
<i>like a member of the legal community.</i>

2497
02:06:55.450 --> 02:06:57.300
<i>I might be able to go on practicing law,</i>

2498
02:06:57.400 --> 02:06:59.800
<i>if I was working with my whole heart.</i>

2499
02:06:59.900 --> 02:07:01.800
<i>But I can't do that and cover Kelly.</i>

2500
02:07:01.900 --> 02:07:06.200
<i>And she's gonna need
a lot of cover for a while.</i>

2501
02:07:07.800 --> 02:07:10.750
<i>I still love the law. I'll always love it.</i>

2502
02:07:10.850 --> 02:07:12.900
<i>But maybe I should be teaching it</i>

2503
02:07:13.000 --> 02:07:16.000
<i>instead of practicing it out here in the world.</i>

2504
02:07:16.500 --> 02:07:18.600
<i>I need time to work it out.</i>

2505
02:07:18.700 --> 02:07:21.300
Great Benefit has gone belly up.

2506
02:07:22.850 --> 02:07:25.450
Barring a miracle way off in the distance,

2507
02:07:25.550 --> 02:07:27.100
we won't get a dime.

2508
02:07:28.300 --> 02:07:29.300
God!

2509
02:07:29.400 --> 02:07:31.650
You've put them out of business, Dot.

2510
02:07:31.750 --> 02:07:34.700
One little woman from Memphis, Tennessee,

2511
02:07:34.800 --> 02:07:37.900
bankrupted them sons of bitches?

2512
02:07:38.000 --> 02:07:39.000
Oh!

2514
02:07:41.000 --> 02:07:45.000
I'm gonna go to Donny Ray's grave
tomorrow and tell him all about it.

2516
02:07:51.700 --> 02:07:56.500
So, I guess Kelly and I will be
taking off first thing in the morning.

2518
02:07:58.400 --> 02:08:00.500
We made history, Rudy.

2519
02:08:01.900 --> 02:08:03.350
You know that?

2520
02:08:05.950 --> 02:08:07.950
We can always brag.

2521
02:08:09.950 --> 02:08:11.450
Bye.

2522
02:08:12.550 --> 02:08:14.250
<i>There's no doubt about it. I'm hot.</i>

2523
02:08:14.350 --> 02:08:16.400
<i>In fact, I'm so hot after this case,</i>

2524
02:08:16.500 --> 02:08:19.250
<i>there's no place for me to go but down.</i>

2525
02:08:19.350 --> 02:08:20.350
See ya.

2526
02:08:20.450 --> 02:08:22.750
<i>Every client I ever have will expect this.</i>

2527
02:08:22.850 --> 02:08:25.950
<i>The same magic, nothing less.</i>

2528
02:08:26.050 --> 02:08:28.450
<i>And I could probably give it to them,</i>

2529
02:08:28.550 --> 02:08:31.150
<i>if it didn't matter how I did it.</i>

2530
02:08:31.250 --> 02:08:32.500
<i>And then one morning,</i>

2531
02:08:32.600 --> 02:08:36.000
<i>I'd wake up and find that
I'd become Leo Drummond.</i>

2532
02:08:36.450 --> 02:08:40.700
Now, you give me a call
when you pass the bar exam.

2533
02:08:41.000 --> 02:08:43.300
Yeah, piece of cake!

2534
02:08:45.600 --> 02:08:48.450
<i>Every lawyer, at least once in every case,</i>

2535
02:08:48.550 --> 02:08:51.600
<i>feels himself crossing a line
he doesn't really mean to cross.</i>

2536
02:08:51.700 --> 02:08:52.850
<i>It just happens.</i>

2537
02:08:52.950 --> 02:08:54.900
<i>And if you cross it enough times,</i>

2538
02:08:55.000 --> 02:08:57.050
<i>it disappears forever.</i>

2539
02:08:58.200 --> 02:09:00.850
<i>And then you're nothing
but another lawyer joke,</i>

2540
02:09:00.950 --> 02:09:04.100
<i>just another shark in the dirty water.</i>
